Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.04,0:00:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.09,0:00:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, about the connection between that Eisuke kid and Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if we go by blood type, Hondou Eisuke's sister and Mizunashi Rena obviously seem to be different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since according to his child health records, Eisuke's blood type is O...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.02,0:00:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, his sister, whose blood was transfused into him, must clearly have type O as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.77,0:00:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, Mizunashi Rena, who's now in the hospital, has AB, so that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.90,0:00:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that kid and Mizunashi Rena aren't siblings after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.12,0:00:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.70,0:00:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're hiding something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.08,0:00:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't make that scary face at me; I'll tell you when I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.50,0:00:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll save my scary face for next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.35,0:01:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As good as always...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.52,0:01:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s singing voice is like little birds chirping.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.36,0:01:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, those crows are back up on the third floor railing again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.16,0:01:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.33,0:01:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up, you bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.38,0:01:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Crow, why do you sing," eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.07,0:01:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tingling suspense is building.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.78,0:02:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running in the darkness —\ha red scream and a black shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.62,0:02:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Mizunashi Rena to the Black Organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The FBI and I make a powerful tag team that drives them against the ropes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.91,0:02:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.41,0:02:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.13,0:02:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.17,0:03:45.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,CLASH OF RED AND BLACK\NCOMA
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stopped at Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.18,0:03:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I called, no one picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:03:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Ran, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.20,0:04:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't contact him by phone and he's breaking the class call chain again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.03,0:04:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plans for the school event we made at the start of the break have been put on hold and we can't contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Again"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long has it been since you were able to reach him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was right after winter break started...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.46,0:04:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko said the call chain had stopped at Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} then too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} say anything before winter break began?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.85,0:04:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he said he'd found a clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.23,0:04:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At Haido Central Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.65,0:04:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haido Central Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where Mizunashi Rena is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.49,0:04:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place where they've hospitalized that member of the Black Organization, otherwise known as Kir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.33,0:04:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did he find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.45,0:04:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The FBI was supposed to be hiding her there discreetly, so no one would know her whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.67,0:04:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't have been that easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:04:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.17,0:05:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear what I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clue wasn't about Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.55,0:05:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.10,0:05:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.35,0:05:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he found a member of his father's company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.61,0:05:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe ever since he lost contact with him, his father and his people from his company have been looking for his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.24,0:05:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of his father's colleagues...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A member of the "Company"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.54,0:05:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that aside from those guys in black...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Company" is also searching for Mizunashi Rena?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was after that, that we stopped being able to contact Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.09,0:05:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he and that colleague and have been searching for his sister together during the winter break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.56,0:05:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For making you come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.18,0:05:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.48,0:05:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talking on the phone near the hospital is risky, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.15,0:06:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I have something I want to tell you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is that's bothering you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Hondou Eisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone to Haido Central Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.87,0:06:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy that's looking for his sister that resembles Mizunashi Rena, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.62,0:06:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that he visited the hospital at the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.71,0:06:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.58,0:06:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He showed some nurses his sister's photo and asked about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since they didn't know that Mizunashi Rena was there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't have been able to tell him anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.47,0:06:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not talking about his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.31,0:06:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he saw a colleague of his father's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.19,0:06:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.27,0:06:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the "Company"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's become likely they are searching for Mizunashi Rena as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know their intentions, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.65,0:06:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could really be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.99,0:06:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's the "Company," then they may know the faces of us FBI agents...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:07:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys stop at nothing, so I wouldn't put it past them to do something rough, even if it's in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I\NThen, it's likely that Mizunashi Rena's location could be exposed to those guys in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.05,0:07:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be fine if it they'd just stopped into Haido Central Hospital for a visit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if they're hiding inside, we have to take measures quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.01,0:07:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, I've been wondering...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.93,0:07:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this "Company"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From listening to you two, I gather that it's not the usual sort of company...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.73,0:07:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as the FBI is known as a "bureau," they are known as a "company."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They gather intelligence in support of the policies of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The intelligence service that carries out foreign activities under the direct control of the President.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By that, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.79,0:07:44.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The CIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.29,0:07:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The CIA!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.30,0:07:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that Eisuke's father is an American spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what you meant?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.30,0:07:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but that's just one possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.85,0:08:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.23,0:08:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sounded out various places and finally got a hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.48,0:08:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.77,0:08:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His real name: Ethan Hondou.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.61,0:08:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a second-generation Japanese-American that joined the CIA thirty years ago as a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.03,0:08:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years after that he came to Japan, got married, and went into hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't find out what he was looking for here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.62,0:08:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Intelligence on the Black Organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.63,0:08:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you trust the story that the CIA is pursuing Mizunashi Rena's whereabouts as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.47,0:08:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.72,0:08:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that Eisuke-kid is searching for Mizunashi Rena, a partner of those guys who got plastic surgery to look like his sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.39,0:08:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't the CIA have stopped him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.02,0:08:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.23,0:08:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the Organization is pursuing her whereabouts as well, he would be in danger if they noticed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could hinder the CIA's operations as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if he's really their operative's son, there'd be no reason not to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.03,0:09:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they probably did stop Hondou Eisuke from finding Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he saw a colleague of his father's at Haido Central before winter break...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which was right before we lost contact with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.46,0:09:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the CIA stopped him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.97,0:09:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're probably protecting him now as they were requested to by his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.02,0:09:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy's father, Ethan Hondou...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Died four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an abandoned warehouse in Yokohama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.45,0:09:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eye-witness was a homeless man who was sleeping on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.37,0:09:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After being awoken by a gunshot, he looked to the bottom floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.41,0:09:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A woman was crouching near the collapsed body of a man, when two other men entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both were wearing black.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.34,0:09:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One was tall, with long hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.38,0:09:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other was of a solid build and wearing sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kneeling woman explained to the two men in a feeble tone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.10,0:10:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I bit into his wrist..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.06,0:10:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Grabbed his gun..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And shot him to death."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.65,0:10:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she said, "I didn't say anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Listen to the MD the dead man is carrying and you'll know."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.58,0:10:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a while, another man appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.33,0:10:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He rushed over and began calling out...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.67,0:10:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hondou!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.09,0:10:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hondou," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.17,0:10:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the man who rushed over was with the CIA also?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he just called out his last name, how do you know it was really Ethan Hondou?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.18,0:10:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I showed him the picture of Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s father you sent me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.56,0:10:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I showed it to him for confirmation, he said it was certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.94,0:10:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He found conclusive evidence that Ethan Hondou was a CIA operative.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:11:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how he got it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His evidence has never proven wrong —\hnot even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I doubt they would leave a witness alive, much less two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.33,0:11:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Luckily, they didn't realize the homeless man was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they did kill the man who rushed to the body from where they were hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They burned down the warehouse as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.97,0:11:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must have expected anyone alive inside to go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.39,0:11:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aside from that, the kneeling woman proved even more surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.69,0:11:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That homeless man, though he was scared to do so, finally responded:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That woman kneeling there was the splitting image of that announcer, Mizunashi Rena."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.41,0:11:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As we thought, Mizunashi Rena's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it would seem she's not that Eisuke kid's sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:52.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she were, that would mean the daughter shot and killed her own father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.54,0:11:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking about it, she must have impersonated Ethan Hondou's daughter to get close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.59,0:12:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was probably sounding out Row much the CIA understood of the situation, but was then found out and captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose that before he could make her talk, she fought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm stuck now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.19,0:12:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to ask Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} more details about his father and thought you could call him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.15,0:12:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now we can't contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.40,0:12:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, let's head to Haido Central Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since CIA members may be hiding there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could prove useful since they don't know my face, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be there in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as you ordered, I have that nurse that Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} showed the photo waiting for us, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.85,0:12:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I not your boss anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.90,0:12:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Driver, did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.11,0:13:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, doesn't it worry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.23,0:13:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did this Eisuke boy disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's why I'm going to listen to that nurse's story first and get on the right track.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But right now, I think the CIA is protecting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.37,0:13:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although his father may be dead, I think there must be an operative who knows his colleague's son's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if Hondou Eisuke just saw a colleague of his father's at the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.89,0:13:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember, when Hondou Eisuke was younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked about his father taking him to that Okonomiyaki place...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.02,0:13:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, isn't this the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.60,0:13:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah. This is the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was where his father brought his CIA colleagues, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he brought his son with him, it was just the two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.08,0:13:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he never saw the faces of his father's CIA colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if his father never introduced him to his partners...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.09,0:14:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would he have seen one of his partners at the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.38,0:14:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he found a clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.76,0:14:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to what Ran said, he didn't "see" anyone, he "found a clue."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That probably means he didn't see anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, what did he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.81,0:14:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By saying he found a clue to a member of his father's company...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.15,0:14:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The father told his colleagues at the Okonomiyaki shop, "I'll dive in deeper."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he really meant, "I will finally get into the Black Organization."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.04,0:14:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.54,0:14:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} definitely said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "I found a member of my father's company."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.96,0:14:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would that be because he saw someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.59,0:14:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of his father's business colleague's mail address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.89,0:14:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said someone at the Haido Central Hospital punched in the same address.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.93,0:14:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A company employee's?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:15:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would he know the e-mail address without seeing the person?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.10,0:15:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.85,0:15:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he had been overseas for work, his father would call him occasionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During one of these calls, he heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The push tones closely resembled a melody.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.08,0:15:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Melody?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right, a children's song.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.59,0:15:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,(SEVEN CHILDREN)\N"Nanatsu no Ko"!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was that tune?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.34,0:15:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked, and his father said he was mailing one of the guys at his company on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.72,0:15:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person Eisuke saw at Haido Central Hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person hiding there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of their operatives is in this hospital, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.95,0:15:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they may not be still hidden there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.00,0:16:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could have only been a brief visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.21,0:16:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we be confident in your source?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Edogawa Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy he knows witnessed someone at the Haido Central Hospital punching in the e-mail address of the Organization's boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.89,0:16:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kid again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're infatuated with him, Jodie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.56,0:16:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, I have the nurse who spoke with that boy waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Avoid taking any conspicuous action before we arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.52,0:16:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Convey that to the other agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's revealed that Mizunashi Rena is being sheltered by the FBI in that hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.61,0:16:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only line connecting us to the Organization may be cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.34,0:16:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our only line, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:17:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we only dangle a line in a dark sea, we won't catch anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.28,0:17:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To reel them in, we need a line with...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bait that tempts them from deep in their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.87,0:17:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hook that goes deep inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.84,0:17:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.96,0:17:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came at the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a photo of a girl with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.80,0:17:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did he say that it was a photo of the announcer Mizunashi Rena?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.51,0:17:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked if she was hospitalized here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him she wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she were here, everybody in the hospital would be talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought: He wasn't searching for his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.15,0:17:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's after Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.66,0:17:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That this boy went missing after coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.91,0:18:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's not missing, we just lost contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why his teacher and neighbors are looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.50,0:18:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, Mizunashi Rena has been on break from TV for a long time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he got the idea that she might be in a hospital somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.14,0:18:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a big fan of hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he's been out searching and has hardly been home since his winter break started.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.90,0:18:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he say anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.61,0:18:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was asked about the same thing that you're asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.03,0:18:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I saw someone who looked like Mizunashi Rena in this hospital. Is it really her?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seemed really surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see him well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.05,0:18:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.22,0:19:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran into someone, which caused one of my contacts to fall out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he came up and asked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.27,0:19:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And his voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.65,0:19:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.98,0:19:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember it was a man, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.86,0:19:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he must have been a patient hospitalized at the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.53,0:19:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, the shop got in some new sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could faintly see that those were the one's he was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.08,0:19:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did the shop start selling those sandals?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.63,0:19:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.21,0:19:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was from the 18th of December.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then there really is a member of the Organization hiding here in this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.30,0:19:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.02,0:19:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to transfer Mizunashi Rena to a different place immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.11,0:20:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing as we know there's a member of the Organization hiding here, we'd be taking too great a risk leaving her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.95,0:20:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if we make any sudden moves, we'll be announcing to them that she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.70,0:20:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if there is a hospital who will allow us to admit her, we could do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better to leave her here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.38,0:20:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Leave her here"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After having someone become a patient...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And seeing as they've only asked a nurse a leading question about Mizunashi Rena's whereabouts...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must still be in the initial investigation phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.97,0:20:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They came here in order to get decisive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.02,0:20:31.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, this is our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.85,0:20:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.06,0:20:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To add a second line to the one we already possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I do think it's best that we catch him before he discovers us, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.24,0:20:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there were more than twenty male patients admitted to this hospital at the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.95,0:20:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, investigating each of them without making it known we're with the FBI makes things difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.62,0:20:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, it would take too much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.83,0:21:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only that nurse could remember which day that man made the inquiry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.01,0:21:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was one of the four days between December 18th and December 21st.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.56,0:21:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The winter break for Teitan High School started on December 23rd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.48,0:21:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} came here before the school's winter break, so he must have come before the 21st.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.53,0:21:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If those sandals were only introduced in the shop on the 18th,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.24,0:21:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we should focus on those hospitalized between the 18th and 21st, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.87,0:21:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll get a list of those hospitalized during that period from the director right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.54,0:21:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's left of concern to us is the whereabouts of that Eisuke boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.88,0:21:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as an FBI agent, I say it's more convenient if he stays gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having the son of a NOC hanging about would present various obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NOC?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.27,0:21:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Non-official cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.14,0:21:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NOC, for short
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.65,0:22:02.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's used for secret agents that appear as civilians and infiltrate other countries for assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.19,0:22:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know so many things; could this be your first time hearing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.70,0:22:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I have, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.82,0:22:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That word...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.87,0:22:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Non Official Cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.62,0:22:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NOC, for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.21,0:22:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that boy is getting close enough to know their boss's e-mail address...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.13,0:22:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys have no reason to leave him alone.
